        "S2365": {
          "id": "S2365",
          "shortDescription": "Properties should not make collection or array copies",
          "fullDescription": "Most developers expect property access to be as efficient as field access. However, if a property returns a copy of an array or collection, it will be much slower than a simple field access, contrary to the caller’s likely expectations. Therefore, such properties should be refactored into methods so that callers are not surprised by the unexpectedly poor performance.",
